JOHANNESBURG &#8211; The firing of South African Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan is &#8220;totally unacceptable&#8221; and President Jacob Zuma made the decision because of a &#8220;dubious&#8221; intelligence report, Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa said on Friday.Ramaphosa said he told Zuma that he disagreed with his decision to sack Gordhan.&#8220;I told the president so, that I would not agree with him on his reasoning to remove the minister of finance,&#8221; Ramaphosa told reporters.Ramaphosa also told reporters that he would not resign following the cabinet reshuffle.&#8220;I&#8217;m staying to serve our people,&#8221; he said.Ramaphosa also told public broadcaster SABC TV that the government would remain stable and would tell ratings agencies that its institutions were strong.